title: Christopher Williams
description: When the body of a young boy is found in the harbor, Ali tries to tie the case to the similar unsolved murder of Christopher Williams in 1977.

title: Janine Elston
description: Ali investigates the 12-year-old murder of a ex-detective's daughter, which destroyed his career.

title: Tess
description: Ali takes on the case of a teen-aged Jane Doe, whom Tony has named "Tess," whose body was discovered 15 years earlier.

title: Jane Klosky
description: Ali and Tony examine the similarities between two cases where women were beaten and decapitated.

title: Taggert Family
description: Ali revisits the case of Barbara Taggert, a mother who was killed in a house fire in 1995 that was ruled an arson. Her daughter Lisa disappeared that night and was presumed abducted.

title: Salty Cheever
description: While investigating a 1995 murder, Ali and Tony come upon a new lead on a suspect in the 1968 murder of a sailor in his cheap hotel room.

title: Amanda Millerd
description: Ali reopens a closed case when a woman who was assumed to be dead since 1982 is arrested after a routine traffic stop. The identity switch leads to someone within the police department.

title: Marcey Bennett
description: Ali reopens a closed case after she is shown a police video that indicates forensic malfeasance by the lead detective and the profiler.

title: Chantal LaMorande
description: When a man comes to the station with a box containing a blood-stained dress with a bullet hole, Ali and Tony investigate a possible murder on the college campus in 1964. They discover the victim wasn't who she appeared to be.

title: Willy Santayana
description: When a Chinese teenager is found hanging in a jail cell the morning after being arrested, Ali and Tony investigate the similarities with another jail cell hanging 20 years before, when the police department was being investigated for brutality.

title: Dwayne Douglas Smith
description: Ali and Tony check out the story of an informant who claims he knows who killed a tow truck operator in 1991. Their case turns on the testimony of a woman who was a drug addict then, and who is now a hyper-religious housewife.

title: Edmund Kritch
description: When an abandoned warehouse is being torn down, a headless corpse is discovered sealed in an interior wall. Tony concludes that the body is an industrialist missing since July 1972.

title: Marilyn Larson
description: When a young woman claims to have a 17-year-old "recovered memory" of her sister's murder, the whole squad tries to sort through the family's secrets. Meanwhile, Ali attempts to get a confession from a terminally ill man long suspected of being a hit-man.

title: The Kowalchuck Boy
description: Firemen responding to a house fire find a child's picture displayed on a computer. Ali's attention is aroused when the child is identified as a boy who disappeared and was declared dead 15 years before, but in the picture he is older than when he disappeared.

title: Douglas Somerset
description: After a body is found at a construction site excavation, Ali and Tony look into the case of an Anglican priest missing for two years. Simon asks Ali out on a date after accompanying her to an official function.

title: Bobby Johnson
description: After a social worker asks Ali for her opinion on a possible child abuse case, Ali looks into the death of a little boy three years earlier in the same household.

title: Gavin MacInnis
description: Against her objections, Ali is given the job of investigating a doctor, whose husband died in a hospice, after one of her patients dies under nearly identical conditions in the same hospice.

title: Nancy Seniuk
description: After reading a letter from a recently deceased hit-man, Ali connects the murder of an elderly woman to the murders of several informants used in a drug task force Simon ran in the 1980s, and finds out there is an leak within the police force.

title: Deadly Games: Part 1
description: After being informed by Simon that the Cold Squad is being folded into other units, and that her position has been eliminated, Ali storms out of Dick's tavern. Digesting the news while driving her car, she hits a teen-aged boy standing in the street.

title: Deadly Games: Part 2
description: While Ali is suspended and Tony recovers from gunshot wounds, Coscarella investigates the source of the automatic weapons, and he runs into another agency on the same trail.

title: First Deadly Sin
description: While Ali copes with the loss of her partner and Coscarella's undermining of her authority, Mickey fends off the unwanted affections of a defense attorney. Nicco investigates a murder involving a large wrench.

title: The Naked and the Dead
description: Ali is determined to build a murder case against a rock star, with or without Frank's help. Mickey and Nicco track down a man who deliberately wrecked his car for the insurance money, killing a child in the back of a parked car in the process.

title: Deadbeat Walking
description: A man up for parole after 2-1/2 years of an eight year sentence for sexual assault wants a deal for information he has on the murder of two 14-year-old girls.

title: Death, a Love Story
description: Internal Affairs starts an investigation after Ali fires her weapon at an unarmed suspect during a raid at a grow house.

title: Pretty Fly for a Dead Guy
description: When a car is pulled out of a lake, Ali and Nicco look into the hit-and-run death nine years earlier of an aspiring rap artist.

title: Dead End
description: When a fugitive from the US is captured, Ali investigates his claims that he killed two girls in Canada. If she proves his claim, he will serve life in a Canadian prison; if not, he will be extradited to face the death penalty in California.

title: The Good, the Bad and the Dead
description: Ali, Mickey, Nicco, and Frank each question a former foster child about a house fire that killed their foster mother 20 years before.

title: Death by Intent: Part 1
description: Ali and Frank try to connect the murder of a sex worker in Blood Alley to a serial murderer they investigated years before. Bailey's daughter sees Mickey and Bailey kissing on a crowded sidewalk and confronts them.

title: Death by Intent: Part 2
description: After Anita is found murdered, Frank and Nicco take it upon themselves to prove Lance did it, even though, as an active murder case, it is not within their jurisdiction.

title: A Good Death
description: Firemen discover 8 bodies wrapped in plastic in a house. Mickey falls under suspicion when Bailey's wife is murdered, and Bailey doesn't back up Mickey's alibi.

title: Common Knowledge
description: Frank and Ali reopen the case of Leonard Larkin, whose son was acquitted of his murder and now claims his sister killed their father, and that her husband gave her a false alibi. Mickey's case is referred to Homicide.

title: Murder Farm
description: An unidentified body is found at the forensic "body farm", and Ali and Mickey are assigned the duty of identifying it and determining manner of death.
Ali works with a visiting Russian detective to connect the dots between the Russian Mob and a traffic accident that killed a Russian hockey player.

title: Loyalties
description: Mickey and Ali check out the story of a career criminal who wants to be sent back to prison for murder. Frank looks into a case that involved Nicco back in his undercover days.

title: Slave to the Job
description: Ali, Frank, Nicco, and Mickey try to connect a cold murder case to a massage parlor that employs immigrant women as indentured servants.

title: Trust
description: Ali and Mickey reopen a 12 year old case, which was originally judged a murder-suicide, based on the word of an arrested drug dealer. After a man reports being attacked by a dog, Frank investigates whether the dog-owner earlier had killed his wife by ordering the dog to attack her.

title: Court Appeal
description: After the evidence against a rape/murder suspect is thrown out on a technicality, Frank must find another witness, and he must persuade the witness to come back to Canada to testify.

title: Root Cause
description: Mickey is severely beaten while trying to make an arrest with Ali. Frank and Nicco investigate a death within a polygamist family.

title: My So Called Death
description: Ali and Mickey look into a three-year-old suicide case when a letter surfaces taking credit for pushing the victim off a bridge.

title: Loose Ends: Part 1
description: Mickey and Ali investigate the connection between a woman's murder outside an antique shop and a car chopping outfit.

title: Dead Soldiers
description: Frank gets personally involved in a seven year old case when a man comes to collect the personal effects of his father, who was awarded the Victoria Cross for his heroism during the Normandy Invasion in 1944.

title: Checkmate
description: The building is locked down after two prisoners overpower their custodians, take a weapon, and shoot an officer.

title: The Box
description: Ali and Frank interrogate Danny Cullen, a former undercover cop, about the murders of two bikers and an RCMP undercover officer.

title: Predators
description: A pedophile comes forward and confesses to the murder of a boy 20 years ago, and he then tries to claim the reward the parents had put up to find their boy's killer.

title: The Unsinkable Iwa Gudang
description: Ali and Frank are stuck on a quarantined Polish ship while investigating a crew member's suspicious death, which resembles the death of another crew member whose body washed ashore four years before.

title: Vancouver Confidential
description: The investigation into a prison inmate's killing by a guard who was under the care of a high-profile self-help counselor is complicated by the fact that Mickey is also a client of the counselor. Christine's brother is brought in on a petty beef, and she arranges his release.

title: Habeas Corpus
description: Ali and Mickey are called to the scene when a mutilated body is discovered by a man driving his SUV off-road. Sam later identifies the body as a man Dean Bulmer was convicted of killing on the basis of another body Sam mistakenly identified.

title: Faith
description: A store clerk is murdered after Dean Bulmer is released, and Ali is blamed by the other detectives because she questioned the validity of the case.

title: The Needle and the Debutante
description: Ali investigates the death of a woman involved in the art scene who died of a drug overdose. Tensions mount when Christine embarrasses Mickey in front of the criminology class Mickey is teaching.

title: Bottom Feeders
description: Testifying in a murder trial, Mickey gets burned by the defense attorney. Nicco tries to conceal the circumstances of his uncle's death.

title: The Shed
description: Len has a suspect delivered to him at an abandoned shelter in the forest in order to coerce a confession out of him. Ali and Mickey question a former teacher at Ambleton about the murder of two children there.

title: Dead Letters
description: Mickey tries to convince Harper and Pawlachuk that a pile of old letters holds the key to a teen-aged girl's murder. Ali teams up with a Russian cop to connect stolen Russian historical documents to a murder.

title: Enough Is Enough
description: Nicco risks his police career trying to save Billie from her pimp and from her addiction. Mickey and Ali wrap up the Ambleton case . . . or so they think.

title: Ambleton
description: Ali and the squad attempt to tie the Premier to the murders of Michelle Ripley and Billy Wells, two teenagers at Ambleton.

title: Career Opportunists
description: Ali weighs a job offer in Ottawa.

title: Horton Killed a Wu
description: Mickey adjusts to her new duties as liaison. Billie returns from rehab and wants back into Nicco's life. Ali's attempt to tie a gang wannabe to a double murder goes in a surprising direction.

title: Happily Ever After
description: A woman who Len previously suspected of murdering her wealthy husband returns to town . . . to get married to another wealthy man. Len is determined to stop her before she kills again.

title: Live Fast Die Young
description: Christine's brother Aaron dies after being hit by a car, and she presses for a murder investigation. When that doesn't happen, she infiltrates a group of car street racers without authorization. Len and Ali investigate the death of an infant.

title: Unfaithful
description: When Christine identifies a teen-aged John Doe from a partial skeleton, the boy's mother is someone Pawlachuk knows. His father turns out to be someone everyone in the squad knows.

title: Flamers
description: Len and Nicco work with a homicide detective to look into the connection between a cold murder case and the more recent murder of a gay-bashing thug at the same night club. Mickey uses a new computer program to find an arsonist.

title: Back in the Day
description: A former homicide detective, who was demoted to beat cop 15 years ago for publicly hanging a suspect off a bridge, is promoted to the Cold Squad. He and Nicco work on the case of a body found encased in concrete of a building under construction.

title: Survivor
description: While transporting an accused killer, Ali and Chief Winslow are badly injured when their patrol car crashes in a wooded area.

title: Kill Me Twice
description: Len meets the "victim" of one of his old Homicide cases . . . alive . . . in the holding cell. Mickey is confronted with new developments in a cold case involving a 4-year-old girl, whose decapitated body Mickey found when she was a patrol officer.

title: Bob & Carol & Len & Ali
description: Ali and Len question several members of a swingers club about the death of a financial planner who was also a member. Nicco is cleared to rejoin the squad.

title: Killing Time
description: Ali attempts to build a murder case against John Watts before he is extradited to Texas for the murder of a Texas Ranger and a possible death sentence.

title: True Believers: Part 1
description: Ali is affected by meeting the daughter of a jailed murderer, who commits suicide after pleading his innocence to Ali. Sonia, who is working undercover in a strip club, puts pressure on Len to leave Wanda.

title: True Believers: Part 2
description: Nicco reports for his first day as Acting Sgt. on the beat. Len pumps his snitches for the whereabouts of Valentine by using an offer of $500 for a lead. Ali runs into official interference in the Rhaman suicide investigation.

title: No Life Like It
description: When the sister of a murder victim from a case Ali worked on years before is found dead in an alleyway behind a strip club, Ali investigates the murder even though she's not officially on the police force.

title: Voices Over Water
description: Ali talks to a man about three kids who disappeared from a camp 30 years ago, when he was a counselor, and whose bodies were discovered 4 years later. When she goes to question him further at his residence, she discovers it is a mental hospital.

title: Teen Angel
description: Len and Ali look into the death of a TV talent show contestant who collapsed while performing. Although her death was ruled the result of heart failure, an autopsy at the medical school reveals the cause of death to be poisoning.

title: Cock of the Walk
description: A skeleton is discovered and is identified as the son of a friend of Andy's, a retired Inspector. Ali and Andy quickly determine the boy was working as a male prostitute. Ali is peeved when Ray lists her as a reference without asking her first.

title: Deadbeat
description: After badgering Andy to give her a case as primary investigator, Samantha looks into the case of "Boxcar", a homeless man ruled to have died of "misadventure." Her case hangs on a "bum fight" video tape.

title: Righteous
description: Ray shoots and kills a suspected cop-killer, and Samantha investigates the circumstances of the murder he supposedly committed. A defense attorney persuades Ali to testify in the retrial hearing of a killer she and her former partner helped convict.

title: Girlfriend in a Closet
description: Wanda takes Len to work, and he unexpectedly finds his bags packed in the trunk of the car. Steve Baker, a suspect in the disappearance of a teenage girl three years ago, requests police protection after someone shoots into his house.

title: Mr. Bad Example
description: Len becomes involved with a murder trial because the defendant's previous husband died under circumstances Len ruled a suicide. While his custody hearing is being adjudicated, he becomes romantically involved with the prosecuting attorney.

title: Learning Curve
description: Ray responds to a call of a girl missing from her house, and under Ali's tutelage he uncovers a vital clue. Len and Sam connect the murder of a man to a long-ago World Cup match.

title: Borders
description: After getting himself arrested while on a camp-out in the United States, Harper goes undercover to smoke out marijuana traffickers and in his discussions with the squad soon realises that minor dealers have been dying mysteriously. His objectivity is seriously challenged when he finds himself falling for Lila, the innocent sister of one of the main suspects.

title: C'mon I Tip Waitresses
description: After a taxi driver reports a passenger who seriously gave him the creeps with his misogynistic views on women, Ali decides to look into it, and the trail leads her to Ian Summerhill, a dentist who had dated the first missing woman and had been dating the woman found a couple of days after the cabbie came in. Sam tries to investigate Summerhill's dark side and heads back to her old work place, where girls entertain men for money. Ali's relationship with Paul is threatened when Ian shares some stories of Paul's mis-spent youth with her, and she wonders how accurate they are.

title: The Filth: Part 1
description: While taking his daughter to school, Harper discovers a young girl's body in a box near her school. While he and Ali look into the case, Ali gets creepy cards from "a secret admirer." Sam investigates an abused woman's claims that her husband killed his previous wife in 1999.

title: And the Fury: Part 2
description: Harper searches desperately for his missing daughter Kassia, praying that he will find her before it is too late. Sam has the perfect suspect, a well-known surgeon, but the only witness against him - his wife - is very unstable. Ray's dark side shows itself in dealing with the suspects. Ali makes the choice that will change her life forever.
